IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO IMPROVE THE QUALITY OF LIFE FOR THE POPULATION WITHIN THE SCOPE OF OPERATION THROUGH THE DELIVERY OF HIGH QUALITY ACCESSIBLE COMPREHENSIVE HEALTH CARE.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO IMPROVE THE QUALITY OF LIFE FOR THE POPULATION WITHIN THE SCOPE OF OPERATION THROUGH THE DELIVERY OF HIGH QUALITY ACCESSIBLE COMPREHENSIVE HEALTH CARE. SERVICES INCLUDE MEDICAL, DENTAL, MENTAL HEALTH AND PREVENTIVE HEALTH SERVICES FOR THE ENTIRE FAMILY.
IRS990.Desc: PROVIDED MEDICAL SERVICES TO 26,438 PATIENTS AND DENTAL SERVICES TO 2,153 PATIENTS AND BEHAVORIAL HEALTH SERVICES TO 1,677 PATIENTS IN SOUTHEAST ARKANSAS; SERVED RESIDENTS OF CHICOT, BRADLEY, ASHLEY, DREW, LINCOLN, GRANT & CLEVELAND COUNTIES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, SCHEDULE D, PART X, LINE 2
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MANAGEMENT HAS EVALUATED THEIR INCOME TAX POSITIONS UNDER THE GUIDANCE INCLUDED IN ASC 740. BASED ON THEIR REVIEW, MANAGEMENT HAS NOT IDENTIFIED ANY MATERIAL TAX POSITIONS TO BE RECORDED OR DISCLOSED IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, SCHEDULE I, PART I, LINE 2
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: WE MAKE CONTRIBUTIONS TO LOCAL SCHOOLS AND OTHER LOCAL ORGANIZATIONS. THESE ARE APPROVED BY THE MARKETING MANAGER BASED ON HER BUDGET.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, SCHEDULE J, PART I, LINE 7
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: INCENTIVE PAY IS OFFERED FOR PROVIDERS AND CLINICAL STAFF WHO MEET VARIOUS PRODUCTIVITY GOALS AND FINANCIAL AND QUALITY MEASURES ON A QUARTERLY BASIS. CLINICAL STAFF: LEVEL 1 = $200 LEVEL 2 = $400 LEVEL 3 = $600 LEVEL 4 = $800 INCENTIVE PAY WAS OFFERED TO THE CEO BASED ON LEVEL OF PCMH REACHED, PATIENT GROWTH, AND BOARD EVALUATION. INCENTIVE PAY WAS OFFERED TO THE MEDICAL DIRECTOR BASED ON LEVEL OF PCMH REACHED, PATIENT GROWTH, PATIENT SATISFACTION, AND QUALITY PERFORMANCE. INCENTIVE PAY WAS OFFERED TO THE CFO BASED ON LEVEL OF PCMH REACHED, LEVEL OF PROFIT, AUDIT PERFORMANCE, AND EVALUATION BY THE CEO. PROVIDER BONUSES ARE BASED ON THE NUMBER OF ENCOUNTERS OVER THE MINIMUM REQUIREMENT AND AVERAGE QUALITY METRICS FOR THE QUARTER.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, SCHEDULE M, PART I, LINE 20
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COLUMN B REPRESENTS THE NUMBER OF CONTRIBUTIONS MADE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: CFO REVIEWS FORM 990 AND PRESENTS IT TO THE BOARD FOR REVIEW PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MANAGEMENT INVESTIGATES ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICTS AND TAKES APPROPRIATE ACTION AS NECESSARY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A & 15B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPENSATION COMMITTEE BASES CEO'S COMPENSATION ON THE NUMBER OF SITES SERVED. THE COMMITTEE COMPARES TO OTHER SYSTEMS IN THE STATE WITH REGARD TO THE NUMBER OF SITES SERVED TO DETERMINE COMPENSATION. COMPENSATION COMMITTEE PRESENTS PROPOSED COMPENSATION TO THE BOARD FOR APPROVAL. THERE IS A WRITTEN EMPLOYMENT CONTRACT WHICH PROVIDES FOR AN INCREASE IN PAY AFTER 90 DAYS OF EMPLOYMENT. THE CEO DETERMINES THE CFO'S SALARY. A COMPENSATION REVIEW IS COMPLETED EVERY JUNE/JULY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
